description: This walk follows the newly opened Tomaree Coastal Walk, with options to climb Mount Tomaree and several shortcuts back in case of time constraints.

markers.description: Get the train and bus to Nelson Bay using transportnsw.info.
From the bus stop continue to the intersection with Stockton St.
Follow Stockton St to the left to the pedestrian crossing .
Cross at the traffic lights and continue straight on to the harbour.
There are public toilets at the tourist information to the right of the pedestrian crossing.
Follow the esplanade to right along the restaurants.
From the harbour continue following the footpath along the shore.
There are public toilets at Fly Point Park.
Follow the shared path along Victoria Pde.
Access Little Beach through the carpark to the left.
There are public toilets along Little Beach.
From the end of Little Beach follow Beach Rd to the right to the holiday park cafe.
At the corner of Beach Rd follow the path left to the beach.
Follow Shoal Bay Beach to the right.
A short distance up the beach it is possible to switch to the esplanade along the beach.
There is a public toilet block along the beach across the shops.
There is a cafe and a supermarket across the road at Shoal Bay.
From the shops continue along the esplanade to the wharf.
From the wharf continue along the esplanade to the boat ramp.
From the boat ramp follow the footpath along the carpark at Mount Tomaree.
+1h Optionally enter the Tomaree Track up from the end of the carpark.
On the right of the Tomaree Track follow the steps up to the summit.
From the lookout at the summit return back to the carpark.
From the Mount Tomaree carpark follow the road to the left to the Zenith Beach carpark.
From the gate at the end of the carpark follow the Tomaree Coastal Walk
From the intersection at Wreck Beach continue following Shoal Bay Trail straight on.
Cross the road to Box Beach and continue along Shoal Bay Trail.
At the intersection follow Ocean Beach Trail to the left.
Follow the Tomaree Coastal Walk sign down the side trail on the right.
+1km Optionally climb the dunes ahead for a lookout across the Fingal Spit.
The impressive view from exactly this dune, make the Fingal Spit look irresistible.
markers.title: Tempting, but don't Risk It
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: The side trail ends at a lookout platform across Fingal Bay.
From the lookout platform follow the steps down to the beach.
Follow the Tomaree Coastal Walk to the right along the beach.
Halfway down the beach follow the path off the beach to the surf club.
From the surf club follow the footpath to the left along the beach.
-15km Alternatively follow the footpath right from the surf club for a shortcut back to Nelson Bay.
From the corner of Sylvia Street, follow the Austral St Firetrail to the left.
At the intersection of firetrails follow the boreline trail staight on.
From the end of the boreline trail, follow Kerrigan St and Fingal St back to the Nelson Bay shorefront.
From the corner of Magnus St follow Laidler Walk to the harbour shorefront.
There are public toilets along the reserve.
From the reserve follow the footpath along the beach.
At the headland enter Barry Park on he left.
There are public toilets at Barry Park.
From the toilets follow the Barry Park Track.
From the park sign follow the trail across the headland to the left.
At intersection follow the Tomaree Coastal Walk signs.
Follow Boulder Bay Rd a short distance to the left.
From the right side of Boulder Bay Rd, follow the bushtrail around the wastewater treatment plant.
At the intersecting firetrails continue straight on along the Tomaree Coastal Walk.
Follow the trail along the coastal lookout points.
At Rocky Beach follow the beach access trail to the car park to the right.
+500m Optionally follow the beach access trail to the left to visit Rock Beach.
From Rocky Beach return up the access trail to the carpark.
Follow the path along the carpark to the left.
-6km To save an hour follow Big Rocky Trail from the carpark back towards Nelson Bay.
Follow Skip Pan Trail from the right side of Big Rocky Trail,
From the intersection follow the Anna Bay Boreline to the right.
In case you were wondering where Nelson Bay gets its water from.
markers.title: The Boring Part
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: From the intersection continue along Anna Bay Boreline to the left.
From the intersection with the powerline service trail, follow the Meteorological Station Trail to the left.
From the split, follow Meteorological Station Link Trail to the left.
From the intersection with Gan Gan Powerline Trail, to the right of the open field, follow the bush trail up to Tallean Rd.
Follow the bushtrail up to the trailhead at Tallean Rd.
Follow Tallean Rd to the right.
From left side of Tallean Rd follow the steps down to the cemetery.
From the cemetery follow Stockton St to the right.
At the roundabout follow Stockton St to the left.
Follow Donald St to the left to the bus stop.
From the end of the carpark follow the boardwalk to the left.
At intersections follow the Tomaree Coastal Walk signs to Samurai Beach.
Follow the Samurai Beach Track across the headland to Samurai Beach.
Take the steps down to Samurai Beach.
Cross the beach to the headland on the other side.
On the far side of the beach follow Tomaree Coastal Walk signs up the steps to One Mile Beach.
Follow the markers across the headland to One Mile Beach.
Cross One Mile Beach to the headland on the other side.
One the far side of One Mile Beach take the steps up the headland.
At intersections follow the Tomaree Coastal Walk signs to Boat harbour.
The bushtrail across the headland ends at a lookout platform.
From the viewing platform follow the trail markers across the rocks.
The trail resumes after traversing the rocky section.
Follow Nelson St straight ahead from the end of the trail.
At the intersection follow Boat Harbour Rd to the left.
There are public toilets at the Boat Harbour Beach Reserve.
Cross the carpark at the far end of Boat Harbour Beach.
From the carpark follow Kingsley Dr. to the left.
A the corner of Kingley Dr follow the road left to Kingsley Beach.
From the carpark follow the trail down to Kingsley Beach.
At the far end of Kingsley Beach follow the steps up the headland.
Follow the markers across the headland to Little Kingsley Beach.
From the far end of Little Kingsley Beach follow the Tomaree Coastal Walk signs up the next headland.
Follow the bushtrail across the headland.
From the trailhead follow the Tomaree Coastal Walk sign to Birubi Point.
Follow Pacific St along the beach reserve.
There are public toilets on the right side of Pacific St.
From the end of Pacific St follow the Tomaree Coastal Walk to the left.
From Iris Moore Reserve. Follow the trial along the left side of the shorefront houses.
Past the houses follow the rocks up to the historic cemetery.
Continue on the footpath along the history cemetery.
There are public toilets at Robinson Reserve.
Follow the footpath past Robinson Reserve.
At the intersection follow James Peterson St to the left to the surf club.
There are amenities at the surf club.
Birubi Point marks the official end of the Tomaree Coastal Walk.
Follow James Peterson St back from the surf club.
At the intersection follow Gan Gan Rd to the right to the bus stop. There are public toilets at the nearby carpark.
Plan your return trip from Anna Bay at transportnsw.info.
